C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eextensor hallucis longus\u003C/strong\u003E is the second most medial structure in the anterior compartment of the foot. The most medial structure is the tibialis anterior. The dorsalis pedis artery, deep fibular nerve, and extensor digitorum longus are positioned more laterally compared to the extensor hallucis longus.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The tibialis anterior is the most medial structure in the anterior compartment of the foot.","The extensor hallucis longus is the second most medial structure in the anterior compartment of the foot.","The dorsalis pedis artery, deep fibular nerve, and extensor digitorum longus are more lateral compared to the extensor hallucis longus."],"references":["Patton, K. T., \u0026 Thibodeau, G. A. (2018). Anthony\u0027s Textbook of Anatomy \u0026 Physiology-E-Book: Anthony\u0027s Textbook of Anatomy \u0026 Physiology-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Smith, R., \u0026 Wordsworth, P. (2016). Oxford textbook of clinical and biochemical disorders of the skeleton. Oxford University Press","Sud, A., \u0026 Ranjan, R. (2021). Textbook of Orthopaedics, 2e-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Dandy, D. J., \u0026 Edwards, D. J. (2009). Essential Orthopaedics and Trauma E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","MacGregor R, Byerly DW. Anatomy, Bony Pelvis and Lower Limb: Foot Bones. 2023 May 23. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 32491379"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59860"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18362"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59860","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/59860"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-25T04:56:27+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-25T04:57:01+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11080"}},"content":{"data"